Now I have the complete picture. Here is the precise diagnosis and all three changes:

---

## Diagnosis

The bug has **two layers**, and the existing SCSS has the right *intent* but incomplete enforcement:

**Layer 1 — `.logo` is not fully flex-frozen.** `flex-shrink: 0` prevents it from shrinking, but it does not prevent the flex algorithm from allocating it less *space* than its natural width when the parent flex container is under extreme squeeze. The bulletproof lock is `flex: none` (= `flex-grow: 0; flex-shrink: 0; flex-basis: auto`) **plus** `width: max-content`, which forces the flex item's basis to be exactly its content width — making it genuinely immovable.

**Layer 2 — `.links` is not declared as the absorbing side.** It has `min-width: 0` (good), but it's missing `flex: 1 1 0%`. Without an explicit positive `flex-grow` and a zero `flex-basis`, the browser distributes remaining space using `flex-basis: auto` on both sides, and under a hard squeeze it can still trade space from the logo side. Declaring `.links` as `flex: 1 1 0%` makes it unambiguously the side that gives — the logo never even enters the negotiation.

**Root cause:** AP-066 — *Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text*. The fix pattern AP-066 prescribes is exactly `flex: none` + `width: max-content` on the protected element and `flex: 1 1 0%; min-width: 0` on the yielding container. The existing code applied only half of this (one `flex-shrink: 0`, no `flex-basis` lock, no `width: max-content` on logo, no `flex-grow` on links side).

---

## Fix

### File 1 of 3 — `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  // Prevent the row itself from ever wrapping — logo and links stay on
  // one horizontal line at every viewport width.
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  // ─── IDENTITY LOCK (AP-066) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // "Yilan Gao" is the site's primary identity chrome. It must NEVER wrap or
  // compress under flex pressure at any viewport width — not even on the
  // narrowest squeezed desktop window.
  //
  // Three-part lock:
  //   flex: none          — zero grow, zero shrink, basis = auto (content width)
  //   width: max-content  — resolves flex-basis to exactly the content width,
  //                         closing the gap where `auto` can still be negotiated
  //   white-space: nowrap — applied here on the container as belt-AND-suspenders
  //                         (also applied on logoText itself)
  //
  // The tagline side (.links) carries flex: 1 1 0% and is the designated
  // absorber of all remaining space pressure. See .links below.
  // ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  flex: none;
  width: max-content;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  // Belt-and-suspenders: also locked at this level so the text node itself
  // cannot wrap even if an ancestor constraint leaks through.
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // ─── DESIGNATED ABSORBER (AP-066 complement) ──────────────────────────────
  // This side is explicitly declared as the pressure-absorber for the nav row.
  // flex: 1 1 0% means:
  //   grow: 1  — takes all remaining space (pushes logo left)
  //   shrink: 1 — gives up space first when the row is squeezed
  //   basis: 0  — starts from zero, never from its intrinsic content width
  //
  // min-width: 0 allows it to shrink below its content width so the tagline
  // inside it can wrap to two lines rather than pushing the logo.
  // ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  flex: 1 1 0%;
  min-width: 0;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  flex-shrink: 0; // nav links themselves never compress — only tagline yields
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // The tagline is the designated soft edge of the nav. It yields to narrow
  // viewports by wrapping (max 2 lines). It never pushes the logo.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

